data.name: treeNode122.ToolTipText
data.value: Movements up/down the demand curve means simultaneous change in prices of all final goods and services , not just a single good or service (that would be micro-economics), law of demand – keeping all other goods constant and focusing on a single final good/service

data.name: treeNode129.ToolTipText
data.value: e.g if a large number of houses have been built in recent years, the demand to build more would go down i.e investment spending towards construction will go down, so will the demand for new houses. When existing stock is small, agg demand increases, when large agg demand decreases.

data.name: treeNode155.ToolTipText
data.value: In the long run, in the face of high unemployment cause by lower output, nominal wages will fall causing a positive supply shock, causing the output to reach potential output but keeping the lower price the same.
